BTW, here's something I was considering last night. The space shuttle could not succeed economically. The reason is that it bucks the basic trend of the market. The market generally wants specialized items when they're first introduced. This is often because the item it not yet well understood and benefits from being focused on one task. After a product has been on the market for awhile and the market has become saturated, combination (or &quot;integrated&quot;) products will begin to appear. These are successful because the technologies behind them are well understood in the marketplace. As a result, no significant benefits are lost in the integrated version over the more focused versions.<br>
