With respect to returning to earth's surface, a craft traveling in LEO is traveling at least 17,000 mph.  The shuttle does us rockets for breaking (and Mercury, Gemini, and Apollo all used retrorockets for the same purpose) to break from orbit and start the descent.  But there is not craft yet that powers down - it requires too much fuel to thrust continuously in the upper atmosphere.  That fuel takes away from 'useful' payload mass.  Not every mission goes up almost empty.<br>
