Following Enterprise, the orbiter Columbia was created and it became the first Space Shuttle to fly into Earth orbit in 1981. Four sister ships joined the fleet over the next 10 years: Challenger, arriving in 1982 (destroyed Jan, 1986); Discovery, 1983; Atlantis, 1985; and Endeavour, built as a replacement for Challenger, 1991.<br>
<br>
Challenger was slightly heavier than it's sister ship, though I am not sure about Enterprise.  I believe its orbit was lower than the others, and was not designed to get to the ISS.<br>
<br>
Launch mass is about 4.5 million pounds.<br>
<br>
